{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f564dd44-52e2-4171-801b-9298986fa059","content":"Here are the environment variables and pod spec changes you need:\n\n**Environment variables** (on your container):\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"                          # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/tmp/dumps/%e.%p.%t.dmp\"    # %e=exe, %p=pid, %t=timestamp\n  - name: DOTNET_CreateDumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"      # custom createdump location\n```\n\n**Volume mount** (so dumps survive container restarts):\n\n```yaml\ncontainers:\n  - name: your-app\n    # ... image, ports, etc.\n    volumeMounts:\n      - name: crash-dumps\n        mountPath: /tmp/dumps\nvolumes:\n  - name: crash-dumps\n    emptyDir:\n      sizeLimit: 2Gi      # adjust based on your app's memory footprint\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpPath` tells the NativeAOT runtime where to find `createdump` since it's not at the default SDK location.\n- `MiniDumpType=4` (Full) gives the most debuggable dumps but they're large (~RSS size). Use `2` (Heap) or `1` (Mini) to save space.\n- `emptyDir` is ephemeral — swap for a `PersistentVolumeClaim` if you need dumps to survive pod eviction.\n- The `createdump` binary needs `SYS_PTRACE` capability. Add this to your container's `securityContext` if not already present:\n\n```yaml\nsecurityContext:\n  capabilities:\n    add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"23041f64-68f8-4ac1-b04e-54631c5510eb","outputTokens":480,"requestId":"D81B:2749A7:612BB6A:690D48A:69FBEFEE"},"id":"f48bbd73-8c1e-44ec-8918-e9989fd79510","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:50:48.257Z","parentId":"161af882-e885-4fae-a762-8342c4e3e7a8"}
